1
00:00:01,011 --> 00:00:21,011
【音乐之声】
The Sound of Music - 1965

2
00:02:44,012 --> 00:02:46,742
群山因为音乐…
The hills are alive

3
00:02:47,049 --> 00:02:51,418
充满生气
With the sound of music

4
00:02:51,687 --> 00:02:54,121
唱了…
With songs they have sung

5
00:02:54,423 --> 00:02:59,258
千年的歌
For a thousand years

6
00:02:59,528 --> 00:03:02,691
群山让我的心中…
The hills fill my heart

7
00:03:02,931 --> 00:03:07,459
充满了音乐
With the sound of music

8
00:03:07,736 --> 00:03:14,904
要唱出每支歌
My heart wants to sing Every song it hears

9
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:20,279
我心震荡像鸟儿翅膀
My heart wants to beat like the wings Of the birds that rise

10
00:03:20,549 --> 00:03:23,609
由湖边飞上树
From the lake to the trees

11
00:03:23,819 --> 00:03:28,119
我心叹息
My heart wants to sigh Like a chime that flies

12
00:03:28,390 --> 00:03:32,326
像钟声飘扬
From a church on a breeze

13
00:03:32,594 --> 00:03:36,086
笑声像小溪流过石头
To laugh like a brook When it trips and falls

14
00:03:36,331 --> 00:03:39,823
跌荡抑扬
Over stones on its way

15
00:03:40,102 --> 00:03:43,970
夜晚歌唱
To sing through the night

16
00:03:44,239 --> 00:03:48,005
像云雀祈祷
Like a lark who is learning to pray

17
00:03:48,343 --> 00:03:53,975
当我奔向山里
I go to the hills

18
00:03:54,182 --> 00:04:00,348
心情落寞
When my heart is lonely

19
00:04:00,622 --> 00:04:04,490
我听到…
I know I will hear

20
00:04:04,693 --> 00:04:09,187
昔日歌声
What I've heard before

21
00:04:09,464 --> 00:04:14,197
我心就会歌唱
My heart will be blessed

22
00:04:14,436 --> 00:04:22,207
因为音乐的响起
With the sound of music

23
00:04:23,278 --> 00:04:28,443
我要再度…
And I'll sing...

24
00:04:28,650 --> 00:04:37,615
歌唱
...once more

25
00:09:19,674 --> 00:09:24,634
哈利路亚，哈利路亚
Hallelujah, hallelujah

26
00:09:24,913 --> 00:09:29,577
哈利路亚，哈利路亚
Hallelujah, hallelujah

27
00:09:31,786 --> 00:09:33,845
-院长 -柏尼丝修女
- Reverend Mother. - Sister Bernice.

28
00:09:34,089 --> 00:09:36,717
-我找不到她 -犸莉亚？
- I simply cannot find her. - Maria?

29
00:09:37,792 --> 00:09:39,089
她又不见了
She's missing again.

30
00:09:40,028 --> 00:09:42,394
也许我们该在她脖子上 挂个牛铃
We should've put a cowbell around her neck.

31
00:09:42,631 --> 00:09:45,691
你找过仓了吗？ 她很喜欢动物
Have you tried the barn? You know how much she adores the animals.

32
00:09:45,967 --> 00:09:48,697
我到处都找过了
I have looked everywhere. In all of the usual places.

33
00:09:48,903 --> 00:09:51,133
修女，你要知道她是莉亚…
Sister, considering it's Maria...

34
00:09:51,439 --> 00:09:54,033
我建议你找不寻常的地方
...I suggest you look in someplace unusual.

35
00:09:59,314 --> 00:10:00,611
院长…
Well, Reverend Mother...

36
00:10:00,882 --> 00:10:03,442
我希望这次违规 会结束
...I hope this new infraction ends whatever doubts...

37
00:10:03,718 --> 00:10:06,949
你对她在这里 会有未来的疑虑
...you may still have about Maria's future here.

38
00:10:07,155 --> 00:10:11,216
我对疑虑仍常保持信心
I always try to keep faith in my doubts, Sister Berthe.

39
00:10:11,459 --> 00:10:14,326
毕竟黑羊的毛也是会温暖
After all, the wool of a black sheep is just as warm.

40
00:10:14,562 --> 00:10:18,896
我们不是争论绵羊颜色
We are not talking about sheep, black or white, Sister Margaretta.

41
00:10:19,134 --> 00:10:22,570
所有修女的候选人中她最糟
Of all the candidates for the novitiate, Maria is the least...

42
00:10:22,837 --> 00:10:25,328
各位…
Children, children.

43
00:10:25,807 --> 00:10:29,766
我们想了解在修道院的各人 表现如何
We were speculating about the qualifications of our postulants.

44
00:10:30,412 --> 00:10:33,404
见习修女和修道院修女的主管
The Mistress of Novices and the Mistress of Postulants...

45
00:10:33,648 --> 00:10:38,950
表达了不同的意见来协助我
...were trying to help me by expressing opposite points of view.

46
00:10:39,187 --> 00:10:42,247
凯萨琳修女，告诉我 你认为犸莉亚如何？
Tell me, Sister Catherine, what do you think of Maria?

47
00:10:42,457 --> 00:10:45,517
她有时候是个好女孩
She's a wonderful girl, some of the time.

48
00:10:46,494 --> 00:10:49,588
-雅嘉佛修女？ -犸莉亚讨人喜欢
- Sister Agatha? - It's very easy to like Maria...

49
00:10:49,831 --> 00:10:52,356
但有时候却不易相处
...except when it's difficult.

50
00:10:52,667 --> 00:10:56,228
-苏菲亚修女，你呢？ -我喜欢她
- And you, Sister Sophia? - Oh, I love her very dearly.

51
00:10:56,438 --> 00:10:59,373
但她爱惹麻烦
But she always seems to be in trouble, doesn't she?

52
00:10:59,607 --> 00:11:01,199
这就是我要说的
Exactly what I say.

53
00:11:01,676 --> 00:11:04,144
她会爬树伤了膝盖
She climbs a tree and scrapes her knee

54
00:11:04,346 --> 00:11:06,041
衣服裂开
Her dress has got a tear

55
00:11:06,715 --> 00:11:10,879
在往弥撒的路上跳华尔兹 在阶梯上吹口哨
She waltzes on her way to Mass And whistles on the stair

56
00:11:11,519 --> 00:11:16,013
帽巾下，头发会卷着发卷
And underneath her wimple She has curlers in her hair

57
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:20,887
她会在修道院内唱歌
I've even heard her singing In the abbey

58
00:11:21,129 --> 00:11:23,120
她上教堂总是迟到
She's always late for chapel

59
00:11:23,365 --> 00:11:25,629
可是悔却出自真心
But her penitence is real

60
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:28,232
她做什么都迟到
She's always late for everything

61
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:30,495
但每餐饭从不迟到
Except for every meal

62
00:11:30,872 --> 00:11:35,571
我不愿说，但我深深觉得
I hate to have to say it But I very firmly feel

63
00:11:35,810 --> 00:11:40,247
犸莉亚不适合修道院
Maria's not an asset to the abbey

64
00:11:40,749 --> 00:11:43,240
我愿为她说句好话
I'd like to say a word in her behalf

65
00:11:43,518 --> 00:11:44,849
请说，犸格丽特修女
Say it, Sister Margaretta.

66
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:49,679
犸莉亚令我发笑
Maria makes me laugh

67
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:56,496
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

68
00:11:56,765 --> 00:12:00,565
你要如何摘下浮云 然后钉牢？
How do you catch a cloud And pin it down?

69
00:12:00,869 --> 00:12:04,202
你要如何用言语形容她？
How do you find a word That means Maria?

70
00:12:04,739 --> 00:12:05,831
捣蛋鬼！
A flibbertigibbet

71
00:12:06,074 --> 00:12:07,405
-鬼灵精 -小丑
- A will-o'-the-wisp - A clown

72
00:12:09,043 --> 00:12:12,774
许多事你们想告诉她
Many a thing you know You'd like to tell her

73
00:12:13,047 --> 00:12:16,505
许多事她该明t
Many a thing she ought to understand

74
00:12:16,918 --> 00:12:20,615
但如何使她停下听你说完？
But how do you make her stay And listen to all you say?

75
00:12:21,189 --> 00:12:24,681
如何使海浪停留在沙滩上？
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?

76
00:12:24,926 --> 00:12:29,022
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

77
00:12:29,531 --> 00:12:35,060
如何使月光在…
How do you hold a moonbeam...

78
00:12:35,270 --> 00:12:40,731
掌中停留？
...in your hand?

79
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:45,302
当我和她同处就糊涂
When I'm with her I'm confused Out of focus and bemused

80
00:12:45,613 --> 00:12:49,049
茫然不知身在何处
And I never know exactly where I am

81
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:52,583
-如天气难测 -像羽毛飘忽
- Unpredictable as weather - She's as flighty as a feather

82
00:12:52,954 --> 00:12:54,785
-她很可人 -她是恶魔
- She's a darling - She's a demon

83
00:12:54,989 --> 00:12:56,320
她是羔羊
She's a lamb

84
00:12:56,724 --> 00:13:00,387
她让瘟神烦恼，把黄蜂赶出巢
She'll out pester any pest Drive a hornet from its nest

85
00:13:00,595 --> 00:13:03,894
她能使僧侣昏头转向
She can throw a whirling dervish Out of whirl

86
00:13:04,466 --> 00:13:07,993
-她本性善良却又狂野 -她是迷一般的孩子
- She is gentle, she is wild - She's a riddle, she's a child

87
00:13:08,570 --> 00:13:11,130
-她令人头痛 -她是天使
- She's a headache - She's an angel

88
00:13:11,339 --> 00:13:15,241
她只是个女孩
She's a girl

89
00:13:15,977 --> 00:13:19,913
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

90
00:13:20,148 --> 00:13:23,845
你要如何摘下浮云 然后钉牢？
How do you catch a cloud And pin it down?

91
00:13:24,152 --> 00:13:27,644
你要如何用字眼来形容她？
How do you find a word That means Maria?

92
00:13:27,922 --> 00:13:29,913
-捣蛋鬼 -鬼灵精
- A flibbertigibbet - A will-o'-the-wisp

93
00:13:30,158 --> 00:13:31,785
小丑
A clown

94
00:13:32,260 --> 00:13:35,991
许多事你觉得要告诉她
Many a thing you know You'd like to tell her

95
00:13:36,264 --> 00:13:39,756
许多事她应该明t
Many a thing she ought to understand

96
00:13:39,968 --> 00:13:44,302
-但如何使她停下 -听你说完？
- But how do you make her stay - And listen to all you say?

97
00:13:44,539 --> 00:13:48,635
如何使海浪停留在沙滩上？
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?

98
00:13:48,843 --> 00:13:54,679
你要如何处理 像犸莉亚这样的问题人物？
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

99
00:14:10,632 --> 00:14:17,401
如何使月光在…
How do you hold a moonbeam...

100
00:14:18,306 --> 00:14:24,711
掌中停留？
...in your hand?

101
00:14:36,524 --> 00:14:38,515
你可以进去了，犸莉亚
You may go in now, Maria.

102
00:14:51,105 --> 00:14:52,732
过来吧，孩子
Come here, my child.

103
00:14:59,247 --> 00:15:00,612
坐下吧
Now sit down.

104
00:15:01,549 --> 00:15:05,110
院长，我真抱歉 我只是无法自制
Reverend Mother, I'm sorry. I couldn't help myself.

105
00:15:05,386 --> 00:15:08,355
-山峦在呼唤我… -亲爱的
- The hills were beckoning and before... - Dear.

106
00:15:08,756 --> 00:15:10,724
我不是要你来此道歉的
I haven't summoned you for apologies.

107
00:15:10,959 --> 00:15:13,189
请让我忏悔吧
Please let me ask for forgiveness.

108
00:15:13,861 --> 00:15:15,089
如果会让你好过些的话
If you'll feel better.

109
00:15:16,030 --> 00:15:18,396
是的，今日的天空如此蔚蓝
Yes, you see, the sky was so blue today...

110
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:22,433
万物如此碧绿芬芳 我必须成为其中一份子
...and everything was so green and fragrant, I had to be a part of it.

111
00:15:22,704 --> 00:15:27,198
安特斯让我愈爬愈高 好像要我跟它穿过云霄
The Untersberg led me higher like it wanted me to go through the clouds.

112
00:15:27,408 --> 00:15:29,433
万一你在天黑时 迷路怎么办？
Suppose darkness had come and you were lost?

113
00:15:29,711 --> 00:15:31,941
院长，我绝对不会迷路的
Mother, I could never be lost up there.

114
00:15:32,213 --> 00:15:35,046
那是我的山，我在那儿长大的
That's my mountain. I was brought up on it.

115
00:15:35,249 --> 00:15:37,547
就是那座山使我来找你的
It was the mountain that led me to you.

116
00:15:38,319 --> 00:15:41,288
小时我常爬山
When I was a child, I would come down and climb a tree...

117
00:15:41,556 --> 00:15:43,319
眺望你的花园
...and look in your garden.

118
00:15:43,558 --> 00:15:46,493
看着修女们工作 听着她们晚祷的歌
I'd see the sisters at work and hear them sing.

119
00:15:47,829 --> 00:15:51,458
院长，我今天违反规定
Which brings me to another transgression, Reverend Mother.

120
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:53,827
未得准许唱歌
I was singing out there today.

121
00:15:54,502 --> 00:15:58,529
在修道院只禁止见习修女唱歌
Only in the abbey do we have rules about postulants singing.

122
00:15:58,740 --> 00:16:00,765
不论在何处 我似乎都无法停止唱歌
I can't stop wherever I am.

123
00:16:00,975 --> 00:16:03,307
更糟的是 我似乎也无法停止说话
Worse, I can't seem to stop saying things.

124
00:16:03,578 --> 00:16:05,842
所有我想的和我的感觉
Everything I think and feel.

125
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:07,513
有人会认为这是诚实
Some call that "honesty."

126
00:16:07,782 --> 00:16:10,148
但这是很糟糕的，院长
Oh, but it's terrible, Reverend Mother!

127
00:16:10,351 --> 00:16:14,253
你知道贝诗修女总在争论之后 要我吻地板
You know how Sister Berthe makes me kiss the floor after a disagreement?

128
00:16:14,622 --> 00:16:18,114
所以现在我看到她来就吻地板 以节省时间
Lately, I kiss the floor when I see her coming to save time.

129
00:16:20,795 --> 00:16:21,955
犸莉亚
Maria...

130
00:16:22,964 --> 00:16:25,956
当你看到修道院的一切时 想要成为一员
...when you saw us over the wall and longed to be with us...

131
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:30,933
那并不表示你已经准备好 要过这种生活方式，对不对？
...that didn't mean you were prepared for the way we live here, did it?

132
00:16:32,273 --> 00:16:34,673
不，院长 但我祷告，我努力尝试
No, Mother, but I pray and I try.

133
00:16:34,876 --> 00:16:36,605
我也在学习，我真的要做好
And I am learning. I really am.

134
00:16:36,844 --> 00:16:39,506
你在这里学到了 最重要的事是什么？
What is the most important lesson you have learned here?

135
00:16:40,181 --> 00:16:43,981
找出上帝的旨意 全心全意地侍奉主
To find out what is the will of God and do it wholeheartedly.

136
00:16:46,821 --> 00:16:47,947
犸莉亚
Maria...

137
00:16:49,457 --> 00:16:52,221
似乎是上帝的意旨 你要离开我们
...it seems to be God's will that you leave us.

138
00:16:52,493 --> 00:16:53,983
-离开？ -只是短暂的时间而已
- Leave? - Only for a while.

139
00:16:54,495 --> 00:16:56,827
不，院长，别送我走
No, Mother! Please don't send me away!

140
00:16:57,065 --> 00:17:01,331
这里是我的家，我的家庭 我的生命
This is where I belong. It's my home, my family. It's my life.

141
00:17:02,003 --> 00:17:05,029
-你真预备献身上帝？ -我是的
- Are you truly ready for it? - Yes, I am.

142
00:17:05,239 --> 00:17:10,142
或许如果你到外面去看看 就明白我们对你的期望
If you go out into the world for a time, knowing what we expect of you...

143
00:17:10,411 --> 00:17:13,141
你就有机会找出 你对你自己的期望
...you will find out if you can expect it of yourself.

144
00:17:13,347 --> 00:17:17,647
我知道你期望什么，院长 我相信我可以做得到
I know what you expect, Mother, and I can do it! I promise I can!

145
00:17:21,189 --> 00:17:22,417
是的，院长
Yes, Mother.

146
00:17:24,525 --> 00:17:26,186
如果是上帝的旨意
If it is God's will.

147
00:17:28,429 --> 00:17:33,560
萨尔斯堡有个家庭 需要家庭教师一直到九月
There is a family near Salzburg that needs a governess until September.

148
00:17:33,768 --> 00:17:35,998
-到九月？ -照料七个孩子
- September? - For seven children.

149
00:17:36,671 --> 00:17:37,660
七个孩子？！
Seven children?!

150
00:17:37,905 --> 00:17:39,167
你喜欢孩子吗？
Do you like children?

151
00:17:39,941 --> 00:17:41,772
是的，但七个…
Well, yes, but seven!

152
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:46,073
我会告诉范崔普舰长 你明天去
I will tell Captain von Trapp to expect you tomorrow.

153
00:17:46,614 --> 00:17:48,013
舰长？
Captain?

154
00:17:48,716 --> 00:17:53,551
他是皇家海军的退役军官 人很好又很勇敢
A retired officer of the Imperial Navy. A fine man and a brave one.

155
00:17:53,788 --> 00:17:56,518
他太太数年前去世 留下那些孩子给他
His wife died, and he is alone with the children.

156
00:17:56,724 --> 00:18:01,024
我明白他要留住那些家庭教师 会有些困难
I understand he has had a difficult time keeping a governess there.

157
00:18:01,796 --> 00:18:04,094
为何会有困难，院长？
Why difficult, Reverend Mother?

158
00:18:05,466 --> 00:18:08,401
在适当的时机 上帝会让你明白的
The Lord will show you in His own good time.

159
00:18:45,273 --> 00:18:47,741
当主关上门时
When the Lord closes a door...

160
00:18:47,942 --> 00:18:50,467
他会在某处打开窗子的
...somewhere He opens a window.

161
00:18:52,814 --> 00:18:57,808
这天会是如何？
What will this day be like?

162
00:18:58,019 --> 00:19:00,249
我怀疑
I wonder

163
00:19:06,761 --> 00:19:10,857
我的未来呢？
What will my future be?

164
00:19:11,699 --> 00:19:13,963
我怀疑
I wonder

165
00:19:15,536 --> 00:19:18,630
外边的自由逍遥世界
It could be so exciting

166
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:21,934
应该令人兴奋
To be out in the world To be free

167
00:19:22,143 --> 00:19:25,203
我的心该狂欢愉悦
My heart should be wildly rejoicing

168
00:19:26,380 --> 00:19:31,716
我到底是怎么回事？
Oh, what's the matter with me?

169
00:19:32,053 --> 00:19:35,113
我一向渴望着冒险
I've always longed for adventure

170
00:19:35,389 --> 00:19:38,950
做我不敢做的事
To do the things I've never dared

171
00:19:39,193 --> 00:19:42,390
现在我面对着冒险
Now here I'm facing adventure

172
00:19:42,697 --> 00:19:48,795
为何我如此害怕？
Then why am I so scared?

173
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:55,141
一位舰长和七位孩子
A captain with seven children

174
00:19:55,376 --> 00:19:58,209
有何可怕？
What's so fearsome about that?

175
00:20:00,748 --> 00:20:03,376
我必须停止多疑和忧虑
I must stop these doubts and worries

176
00:20:03,651 --> 00:20:06,484
不然，我会回到原点
If I don't I just know I'll turn back

177
00:20:06,754 --> 00:20:09,917
我必须梦想我所追求的事物
I must dream of the things I am seeking

178
00:20:10,992 --> 00:20:15,986
我在追求我所欠缺的勇气
I am seeking the courage I lack

179
00:20:16,898 --> 00:20:20,732
有勇气信赖他们
The courage to serve them With reliance

180
00:20:21,002 --> 00:20:23,903
虚心面对我的错误
Face my mistakes without defiance

181
00:20:24,171 --> 00:20:25,866
让他们知道我的好处
Show them I'm worthy

182
00:20:26,107 --> 00:20:28,769
同时也让自己看见
And while I show them

183
00:20:29,043 --> 00:20:32,843
自己的好处
I'll show me

184
00:20:33,047 --> 00:20:38,451
让他们提出他们的问题
So let them bring on All their problems

185
00:20:38,686 --> 00:20:41,951
我会做得比最好还要更好
I'll do better than my best

186
00:20:42,223 --> 00:20:45,283
我有信心，让他们来考验我吧
I have confidence They'll put me to the test

187
00:20:45,526 --> 00:20:48,962
我会让他们明白，我充满信心
But I'll make them see I have confidence in me

188
00:20:49,196 --> 00:20:52,461
我要使他们印象深刻
Somehow I will impress them

189
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:55,964
我会坚决而和善
I will be firm but kind

190
00:20:56,237 --> 00:20:59,536
上苍祝福那些孩子们
And all those children Heaven bless them

191
00:20:59,774 --> 00:21:03,073
他们会以我为榜样，听我的话
They will look up to me And mind me

192
00:21:03,311 --> 00:21:06,439
每走一步，我更确信
With each step I am more certain

193
00:21:06,714 --> 00:21:09,979
一切事情都会好转
Everything will turn out fine

194
00:21:10,217 --> 00:21:13,311
我有信心世界会由我掌握
I have confidence The world can all be mine

195
00:21:13,554 --> 00:21:18,992
因为我对自己有信心
They'll have to agree I have confidence in me

196
00:21:20,561 --> 00:21:23,291
我对阳光有信心
I have confidence in sunshine

197
00:21:23,564 --> 00:21:26,658
我对雨水有信心
I have confidence in rain

198
00:21:26,901 --> 00:21:29,768
我深信春天会再来
I have confidence That spring will come again

199
00:21:30,071 --> 00:21:33,097
我对自己更有信心
Besides which you see I have confidence in me

200
00:21:33,407 --> 00:21:36,467
力量不存在于数字里
Strength doesn't lie in numbers

201
00:21:36,744 --> 00:21:39,770
力量不存在于财富中
Strength doesn't lie in wealth

202
00:21:40,014 --> 00:21:43,347
力量存在于静夜的酣睡中
Strength lies in nights Of peaceful slumbers

203
00:21:43,617 --> 00:21:46,484
当你醒来就充满精神
When you wake up, wake up It's healthy

204
00:21:46,787 --> 00:21:49,779
我信任心中的指引
All I trust I leave my heart to

205
00:21:50,024 --> 00:21:52,925
就会成为我的
All I trust becomes my own

206
00:21:53,127 --> 00:21:57,928
我对信心更有信心
I have confidence in confidence alone

207
00:22:12,546 --> 00:22:14,173
救命
Oh, help.

208
00:22:26,360 --> 00:22:33,027
我对信心更有信心
I have confidence in confidence alone

209
00:22:33,834 --> 00:22:38,635
况且，你看，我对自己…
Besides which you see I have confidence...

210
00:22:38,906 --> 00:22:45,709
充满信心！
...in me

211
00:22:52,253 --> 00:22:54,653
你好，我来了
Hello. Here I am.

212
00:22:57,491 --> 00:22:59,322
我从修道院来的 我是新的家教，舰长
I'm from the convent. I'm the new governess, captain.

213
00:23:00,995 --> 00:23:04,226
而我是老管家，小姐
And I'm the old butler, fraulein.

214
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,997
你好
Well, how do you do?

215
00:23:18,512 --> 00:23:22,573
请你在此稍候
You'll wait here, please.

216
00:24:48,936 --> 00:24:53,032
以后请记住 这里有些房间是不能乱闯的
In future, remember certain rooms in this house are not to be disturbed.

217
00:24:54,208 --> 00:24:55,675
是的，舰长，先生
Yes, captain, sir.

218
00:25:03,617 --> 00:25:08,850
-你为何如此看着我？ -你看起来一点都不像海上的舰长
- Why do you stare at me that way? - You don't look like a sea captain.

219
00:25:10,057 --> 00:25:13,117
我也认为 你一点都不像个家庭教师
I'm afraid you don't look very much like a governess.

220
00:25:13,827 --> 00:25:14,885
-请转身 -什么？
- Turn around. - What?

221
00:25:15,229 --> 00:25:16,491
转身
Turn.

222
00:25:19,667 --> 00:25:20,827
拿下帽子
Hat off.

223
00:25:24,038 --> 00:25:26,666
你和孩子见面前 最好先换衣服
Put on another dress before meeting the children.

224
00:25:26,974 --> 00:25:28,532
但我没有衣服换了
But I don't have another.

225
00:25:28,809 --> 00:25:31,676
我进入修道院时 将所有衣服送给穷人了
When we enter the abbey, our worldly clothes go to the poor.

226
00:25:31,912 --> 00:25:33,174
这一件呢？
What about this one?

227
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:34,711
穷人不要这一件
The poor didn't want it.

228
00:25:36,550 --> 00:25:40,042
我本想为自己做新衣服的 但时间不够，我会自己做衣服
There wasn't time to make a new dress. I can make clothes.

229
00:25:41,322 --> 00:25:43,586
我会确定你有一些布料的
I'll see that you get some material.

230
00:25:44,325 --> 00:25:45,849
今天，如果可能的话
Today, if possible.

231
00:25:46,827 --> 00:25:48,590
-现在…小姐 -莉亚
- Now, fraulein... - Maria.

232
00:25:48,829 --> 00:25:51,559
我不知道院长告诉了你多少
I don't know how much the abbess told you.

233
00:25:51,832 --> 00:25:54,392
在许多家教中你是第12位了
You are the twelfth governess...

234
00:25:54,602 --> 00:25:57,070
自从他们的母亲去世后 来此照料他们
...to look after my children since their mother died.

235
00:25:57,271 --> 00:25:59,501
我相信你会比上一个更好
I trust you will be an improvement on the last one.

236
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:01,571
她只停留了两小时
She stayed only two hours.

237
00:26:03,277 --> 00:26:05,871
孩子们有何不对吗？
What's wrong with the children, sir?

238
00:26:07,348 --> 00:26:11,751
孩子们都很正常 是家庭教师的错
Nothing is wrong with the children, only the governesses.

239
00:26:12,019 --> 00:26:16,956
她们完全无法维持纪律 没有纪律就不能管好这个家
They could not maintain discipline, without which the house cannot be run.

240
00:26:17,891 --> 00:26:19,688
你得督促孩子学习
Drill them in their studies.

241
00:26:19,927 --> 00:26:23,419
我不准他们虚度假期
I will not permit them to dream away their summer holidays.

242
00:26:23,697 --> 00:26:26,393
下午他们要在庭院操练
Each afternoon, they march, breathing deeply.

243
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:28,261
还要严守就时间
Bedtime is to be strictly observed.

244
00:26:28,469 --> 00:26:29,436
请问他们何时玩耍？
When do they play?

245
00:26:29,637 --> 00:26:33,698
你要看着他们 确定他们循规蹈矩
You will see to it that they conduct themselves with the utmost decorum.

246
00:26:33,941 --> 00:26:36,876
-我要你负责这一切 -是的，先生
- I am placing you in command. - Yes, sir.

247
00:27:57,524 --> 00:27:58,684
现在…
Now...

248
00:27:59,293 --> 00:28:02,228
这位是你们的新家教 犸莉亚小姐
...this is your new governess, Fraulein Maria.

249
00:28:03,897 --> 00:28:05,888
当我吹你们的讯号时 你们踏前一步报出名字
Give your name at your signal.

250
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:10,398
而你要仔细注意那讯号 以便日后召唤他们
Fraulein, listen carefully. Learn their signals so you can call them.

251
00:28:11,705 --> 00:28:13,070
莉莎
Liesl.

252
00:28:13,340 --> 00:28:15,069
费瑞克
Friedrich.

253
00:28:15,342 --> 00:28:16,866
露易莎
Louisa.

254
00:28:17,144 --> 00:28:18,406
寇特
Kurt.

255
00:28:18,645 --> 00:28:19,703
碧姬塔
Brigitta.

256
00:28:19,980 --> 00:28:21,208
犸塔
Marta.

257
00:28:27,588 --> 00:28:28,919
葛特儿
Gretl.

258
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:36,996
现在看看你的耳力如何
Now, let's see how well you listened.

259
00:28:37,231 --> 00:28:39,597
我想我不用哨子的，舰长
I won't need to whistle for them, Reverend Captain.

260
00:28:39,867 --> 00:28:43,325
我会叫他们的名字 尤其是有如此美的名字
I mean, I'll use their names. Such lovely names.

261
00:28:43,537 --> 00:28:46,700
小姐，这是座大房子 地方很宽广
Fraulein, this is a large house. The grounds are extensive.

262
00:28:46,940 --> 00:28:49,704
而我不容许任何人在此喊叫
And I will not have anyone shouting.

263
00:28:49,943 --> 00:28:51,672
请你拿这个，学习使用它
You will take this, please. Learn to use it.

264
00:28:51,879 --> 00:28:53,540
孩子们也会帮你的
The children will help you.

265
00:28:55,582 --> 00:28:59,575
我要找你，你会听到这个讯号
Now, when I want you, this is what you will hear.

266
00:29:00,454 --> 00:29:02,251
不，很抱歉，先生
Oh, no, sir. I'm sorry, sir!

267
00:29:03,123 --> 00:29:04,681
我绝不会听哨子回报的
I could never answer to a whistle.

268
00:29:04,892 --> 00:29:07,520
哨子是用来召唤动物的 但绝不是对孩子
Whistles are for animals, not for children.

269
00:29:07,795 --> 00:29:09,854
而且绝对不会是我
And definitely not for me.

270
00:29:10,097 --> 00:29:12,725
这是种很大的侮辱
It would be too humiliating.

271
00:29:13,534 --> 00:29:18,733
小姐，你在修道院 也是如此麻烦的吗？
Fraulein, were you this much trouble at the abbey?

272
00:29:19,039 --> 00:29:20,131
麻烦得多，先生
Oh, much more, sir.

273
00:29:31,251 --> 00:29:32,809
我不知道你的讯号
I don't know your signal.

274
00:29:34,288 --> 00:29:36,916
你可以叫我舰长
You may call me "captain."

275
00:29:49,837 --> 00:29:51,304
稍息
At ease.

276
00:29:54,107 --> 00:29:55,665
现在只剩下我们
Now that there's just us...

277
00:29:55,943 --> 00:30:00,107
请再一次告诉我你们的名字 还有你们的年龄
...would you please tell me all your names again and how old you are.

278
00:30:00,581 --> 00:30:04,574
我叫莉莎，我16岁 我不需要家教
I'm Liesl. I'm 16 years old, and I don't need a governess.

279
00:30:05,352 --> 00:30:08,412
莉莎，很高兴你告诉我 我们可以做好朋友
I'm glad you told me, Liesl. We'll just be good friends.

280
00:30:10,591 --> 00:30:14,357
我叫费瑞克，我14岁 我是朽木
I'm Friedrich. I'm 14. I'm impossible.

281
00:30:14,661 --> 00:30:16,322
真的？谁告诉你的，费瑞克？
Really? Who told you that, Friedrich?

282
00:30:16,597 --> 00:30:20,089
约瑟芬小姐，前四任教师
Fraulein Josephine. Four governesses ago.

283
00:30:20,534 --> 00:30:22,001
我叫碧姬塔
I'm Brigitta.

284
00:30:23,837 --> 00:30:27,830
你没告诉我你多大，露易莎
You didn't tell me how old you are, Louisa.

285
00:30:28,509 --> 00:30:30,773
我叫碧姬塔，她叫露易莎
I'm Brigitta. She's Louisa.

286
00:30:31,011 --> 00:30:33,775
她13岁，而你很聪明
She's 13 years old, and you're smart.

287
00:30:34,014 --> 00:30:37,780
我10岁，而我认为你的衣服 是我见过最丑的
I'm 10, and I think your dress is the ugliest one I ever saw.

288
00:30:38,118 --> 00:30:40,746
-碧姬塔，你不该这样说的 -为何？
- Brigitta, you shouldn't say that. - Why not?

289
00:30:40,954 --> 00:30:43,218
-你不认为很丑？ -当然
- Don't you think it's ugly? - Of course.

290
00:30:43,490 --> 00:30:46,186
但赫德小姐才是最丑的
But Fraulein Helga's was ugliest.

291
00:30:46,460 --> 00:30:49,054
我是寇特，11岁，我很任性
I'm Kurt. I'm 11. I'm incorrigible.

292
00:30:49,329 --> 00:30:52,457
-恭喜你！ -什么是任性？
- Congratulations. - What's "incorrigible"?

293
00:30:52,699 --> 00:30:56,567
那表示你希望 被人当作是小男孩
I think it means you want to be treated like a boy.

294
00:30:58,739 --> 00:31:02,038
我是犸塔，星期二我就7岁了
I'm Marta, and I'm going to be seven on Tuesday.

295
00:31:02,309 --> 00:31:03,674
我爱粉红色阳伞
I'd like a pink parasol.

296
00:31:04,878 --> 00:31:06,402
纷红色也是我的颜色
Pink's my favorite color too.

297
00:31:08,815 --> 00:31:09,975
是的，你是葛特儿
Yes, you're Gretl.

298
00:31:10,884 --> 00:31:12,579
而你已经5岁了？
And you're five years old?

299
00:31:13,020 --> 00:31:15,011
天啊，你几乎快成为淑女了
My, you're practically a lady.

300
00:31:17,524 --> 00:31:20,550
现在我要告诉你们一个秘密 我从未当过家庭教师
I have to tell you a secret. I've never been a governess.

301
00:31:21,995 --> 00:31:24,759
你一点也不懂如何当家庭教师？
You don't know anything about being a governess?

302
00:31:25,032 --> 00:31:26,397
一点也不懂，我需要许多建议
Nothing. I'll need lots of advice.

303
00:31:27,367 --> 00:31:31,895
首先，就是告诉父亲 要他少管闲事
The best way to start is to tell Father to mind his own business.

304
00:31:32,105 --> 00:31:33,902
你绝对不能准时来用餐
Never come to dinner on time.

305
00:31:34,107 --> 00:31:36,405
喝汤也不要太小声
Never eat your soup quietly.

306
00:31:37,077 --> 00:31:39,170
吃甜点时，要擤鼻子
During dessert, always blow your nose.

307
00:31:39,413 --> 00:31:42,211
别听他们说的话，犸莉亚小姐
Don't you believe a word they say, Fraulein Maria.

308
00:31:42,416 --> 00:31:45,783
-为什么？ -因为我喜欢你
- Oh, why not? - Because I like you.

309
00:31:46,587 --> 00:31:48,578
孩子们，出去散步
Children, outside for your walk.

310
00:31:48,789 --> 00:31:50,689
父亲的命令，快点
Father's orders. Hurry up.

311
00:31:50,891 --> 00:31:52,188
快…
Quick, quick, quick.

312
00:31:52,426 --> 00:31:55,623
犸莉亚小姐 我是蒙思蜜德，女管家
Fraulein Maria, I'm Frau Schmidt, the housekeeper.

313
00:31:55,862 --> 00:31:56,920
你好
How do you do.

314
00:31:57,130 --> 00:32:00,031
我带你去房间，跟我来
I'll show you to your room. Follow me.

315
00:32:11,111 --> 00:32:12,874
可怜的小东西
Poor little dears.

316
00:32:25,592 --> 00:32:29,961
你运气很好 赫德小姐拿到的是条蛇
You're very lucky. With Fraulein Helga it was a snake.

317
00:32:43,810 --> 00:32:45,141
晚安
Good evening.

318
00:32:46,580 --> 00:32:50,141
-晚安，孩子们 -晚安，犸莉亚小姐
- Good evening, children. - Good evening, Fraulein Maria.

319
00:32:57,357 --> 00:32:58,984
很独特的举止
Enchanting little ritual.

320
00:32:59,192 --> 00:33:01,922
是在修道院学来的吗？
Something you learned at the abbey?

321
00:33:03,130 --> 00:33:05,462
不
No.

322
00:33:07,100 --> 00:33:08,362
是风湿
Rheumatism.

323
00:33:18,178 --> 00:33:21,341
对不起，舰长 我们是否忘了向主祷告？
Excuse me, captain. Haven't we forgotten to thank the Lord?

324
00:33:29,556 --> 00:33:32,525
感谢上帝赐给我们一切
For what we receive, may the Lord make us truly thankful.

325
00:33:33,060 --> 00:33:34,994
-阿门 -阿门
- Amen. - Amen.

326
00:33:39,533 --> 00:33:41,467
我要感谢各位
I'd like to thank you all...

327
00:33:41,668 --> 00:33:44,660
今天放在我口袋中的珍贵礼物
...for the precious gift you left in my pocket today.

328
00:33:48,175 --> 00:33:49,972
是什么礼物？
What gift?

329
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:55,241
这是我和孩子们之间的秘密
It's a secret between the children and me.

330
00:33:55,515 --> 00:33:59,144
那我建议你就留着 让我们可以吃饭
Then I suggest you keep it, and let us eat.

331
00:33:59,519 --> 00:34:01,487
我了解陌生人在新家庭里
Knowing how nervous I must have been...

332
00:34:01,722 --> 00:34:04,156
会是有多么紧张
...a stranger in a new household...

333
00:34:04,357 --> 00:34:07,417
了解能被接受 会是多么重要的事
...knowing how important it was for me to feel accepted...

334
00:34:07,694 --> 00:34:11,892
你们使我感到多么温暖
...it was so kind and thoughtful of you to make my first moments here...

335
00:34:12,165 --> 00:34:14,360
快乐和…
...so warm and happy...

336
00:34:14,568 --> 00:34:16,331
欢悦
...and pleasant.

337
00:34:25,579 --> 00:34:27,604
-犸塔，你怎么了？ -没事
- What is the matter, Marta? - Nothing.

338
00:34:40,026 --> 00:34:41,050
小姐
Fraulein...

339
00:34:41,294 --> 00:34:45,128
是不是每餐饭
...is it to be at every meal or merely at dinnertime...

340
00:34:45,365 --> 00:34:49,927
你都想要让我们
...that you intend leading us through this rare and wonderful new world...

341
00:34:50,137 --> 00:34:51,798
消化不良？
...of indigestion?

342
00:34:53,373 --> 00:34:56,240
不，舰长，他们只是很高兴
They're all right, captain. They're just happy.

343
00:35:14,995 --> 00:35:17,657
-劳夫，晚安 -晚安，福兰斯
- Rolfe, good evening. - Good evening, Franz.

344
00:35:17,931 --> 00:35:20,661
-一切正常吗？ -是的
- I trust everything is under control? - Yes, yes.

345
00:35:22,302 --> 00:35:24,736
-有何进展吗？ -或许
- Are there any developments? - Perhaps.

346
00:35:24,938 --> 00:35:27,099
-舰长在不在？ -他在用晚餐
- Is the captain home? - He's at dinner.

347
00:35:27,340 --> 00:35:29,672
-和他的家人？ -是的
- With the family? - Yes.

348
00:35:29,943 --> 00:35:31,740
请立刻把电报交给他
Give him this telegram at once.

349
00:35:32,479 --> 00:35:33,571
没问题
Certainly.

350
00:35:45,258 --> 00:35:46,953
您的电报，先生
A telegram for you, sir.

351
00:35:49,796 --> 00:35:51,627
福兰斯，谁送来的？
Franz? Who delivered it?

352
00:35:51,932 --> 00:35:53,957
当然是劳夫了
That young lad Rolfe, of course.

353
00:35:56,303 --> 00:35:58,032
父亲，我能先告退吗？
Father, may I be excused?

354
00:35:59,005 --> 00:36:03,465
孩子们，明早我必须去维也纳
Children, in the morning I shall be going to Vienna.

355
00:36:03,777 --> 00:36:06,211
怎么又来了，父亲？
Not again, Father!

356
00:36:10,116 --> 00:36:12,175
这次你要去多久，父亲？
How long will you be gone this time?

357
00:36:12,819 --> 00:36:14,286
我不确定，葛特儿
I'm not sure, Gretl.

358
00:36:14,487 --> 00:36:18,048
-是不是去看史蕾特男爵夫人？ -少管闲事
- To visit Baroness Schraeder again? - Mind your own business!

359
00:36:19,025 --> 00:36:20,959
事实上，是的，露易莎
As a matter of fact, yes, Louisa.

360
00:36:22,729 --> 00:36:26,563
-为何我们总见不到男爵夫人呢？ -为何她要见你？
- Why can't we ever see the baroness? - Why would she want to see you?

361
00:36:26,867 --> 00:36:31,736
你会见到她的 我要带她回来这里，和大家认识
You are going to see the baroness. I'm bringing her back with me to visit.

362
00:36:33,240 --> 00:36:35,037
还有麦斯伯伯
And Uncle Max.

363
00:36:35,308 --> 00:36:37,708
麦伯伯
Uncle Max!

364
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:55,091
劳夫
Rolfe!

365
00:36:58,164 --> 00:36:59,222
哦，劳夫
Oh, Rolfe!

366
00:37:01,768 --> 00:37:04,703
-不，莉莎，我们不能 -为何，傻瓜？
- No, Liesl. We mustn't! - Why not, silly?

367
00:37:04,938 --> 00:37:07,600
-我不知道 -你在此不是为了等我吗？
- I don't know... - Isn't this why you're waiting?

368
00:37:07,841 --> 00:37:09,706
是的，当然
Yes, of course.

369
00:37:09,910 --> 00:37:12,708
-我想你，莉莎 -有吗，有多想？
- I've missed you, Liesl. - You have? How much?

370
00:37:12,946 --> 00:37:16,780
好多，我甚至想给你送电报 让我好来此地
I even thought of sending a telegram, so I'd be able to deliver it here.

371
00:37:17,050 --> 00:37:20,952
那是很美好的想法 你为何不做呢？就现在吧
Oh, that's a lovely thought! Why don't you, right now?

372
00:37:21,221 --> 00:37:25,385
-但是我就在此啊 -拜托，劳夫，送给我电报吧
- But I'm here! - Please, Rolfe. Send me a telegram.

373
00:37:25,592 --> 00:37:29,050
我为你起稿：“亲爱的莉莎…”
I'll start it for you. "Dear Liesl..."

374
00:37:29,729 --> 00:37:33,358
亲爱的莉莎 我很想要告诉你…
"Dear Liesl: I'd like to be able to tell you...

375
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:35,795
我对你的感觉，完结
...how I feel about you. Stop.

376
00:37:36,036 --> 00:37:40,564
很不幸，电报费用太贵了
Unfortunately, this wire is already too expensive.

377
00:37:40,774 --> 00:37:42,207
真挚的劳夫
Sincerely, Rolfe."

378
00:37:42,409 --> 00:37:45,173
-真挚？ -衷心的
- "Sincerely"? - Cordially.

379
00:37:45,378 --> 00:37:48,040
-衷心的？ -深情的？
- "Cordially"? - Affectionately?

380
00:37:50,417 --> 00:37:52,442
会不会有回电？
Will there be any reply?

381
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:55,881
亲爱的劳夫，完结
"Dear Rolfe: Stop.

382
00:37:56,890 --> 00:37:59,984
不要完结，你的莉莎
Don't stop! Your Liesl."

383
00:38:01,728 --> 00:38:05,562
如果我们不用等别人 给父亲打电报才能见面就好了
If only we didn't have to wait for someone to send Father a telegram.

384
00:38:05,832 --> 00:38:08,232
我如何知道何时才能见到你？
How do I know when I'll see you again?

385
00:38:09,135 --> 00:38:10,329
让我想想看
Well, let's see...

386
00:38:13,340 --> 00:38:15,308
我可以因为搞错而来
I could come here by mistake.

387
00:38:16,309 --> 00:38:20,939
要给史奈德上校电报 他从柏林来此，停留在…
With a telegram for Colonel Schneider! He's here from Berlin staying with...

388
00:38:21,848 --> 00:38:25,147
没有人知道他在此的 别告诉你父亲
No one knows he's here. Don't tell your father.

389
00:38:25,418 --> 00:38:28,581
-为何不？ -因为你父亲自视为奥地利人
- Why not? - Your father's so Austrian.

390
00:38:28,788 --> 00:38:30,085
我们都是奥地利人
We're all Austrian.

391
00:38:30,290 --> 00:38:34,693
而那些认为该自视为德国人的 他们不希望这样
Some think we ought to be German, and they're very mad at those who don't.

392
00:38:34,928 --> 00:38:36,691
他们已准备好…
They're getting ready to...

393
00:38:38,365 --> 00:38:40,799
我希望你父亲不会惹上麻烦
Let's hope your father doesn't get into trouble.

394
00:38:41,101 --> 00:38:46,004
别担心父亲，他是海军大英雄 他甚至由国王亲自授动
Don't worry. He's a big naval hero. He was even decorated by the emperor.

395
00:38:46,206 --> 00:38:49,471
我不担心他 但我却担心他的女儿
I don't worry about him. I worry about his daughter.

396
00:38:50,010 --> 00:38:51,477
我？为什么？
Me? Why?

397
00:38:51,778 --> 00:38:53,336
-你是那样… -什么？
- Well, you're so... - What?

398
00:38:53,780 --> 00:38:55,270
你是如此地年轻
You're such a baby!

399
00:38:55,715 --> 00:38:58,616
我16岁了，一点都不年轻了
I'm 16. What's such a baby about that?

400
00:39:00,854 --> 00:39:04,381
小女孩在空虚的舞台等待
You wait, little girl On an empty stage

401
00:39:04,624 --> 00:39:07,991
等待命运的开始
For fate to turn the light on

402
00:39:08,628 --> 00:39:11,859
你的生命目前是空白的一页
Your life, little girl Is an empty page

403
00:39:12,132 --> 00:39:16,193
男人希望在上面书写
That men will want to write on

404
00:39:16,903 --> 00:39:22,398
书写
To write on

405
00:39:23,343 --> 00:39:27,279
你16岁，快17岁了
You are 16 going on 17

406
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:31,314
宝贝，该去思考了
Baby, it's time to think

407
00:39:31,518 --> 00:39:35,147
应当警觉，谨慎和当心
Better beware Be canny and careful

408
00:39:35,388 --> 00:39:39,017
宝贝，你正在边缘
Baby, you're on the brink

409
00:39:39,359 --> 00:39:43,193
你是16岁，快17岁
You are 16 going on 17

410
00:39:43,396 --> 00:39:47,059
男孩们会排队等候
Fellows will fall in line

411
00:39:47,367 --> 00:39:50,700
很积极的年轻人 和一些鲁莽小人
Eager young lads And roues and cads

412
00:39:50,904 --> 00:39:54,840
会向你献酒和美食
Will offer you food and wine

413
00:39:55,108 --> 00:39:58,874
你完全没有心理准备
Totally unprepared are you

414
00:39:59,279 --> 00:40:02,840
去面对男人的世界
To face a world of men

415
00:40:03,416 --> 00:40:07,580
怯懦和害羞，你会如此的畏惧
Timid and shy and scared are you

416
00:40:07,887 --> 00:40:11,379
事情全在你知识范围以外
Of things beyond your ken

417
00:40:11,591 --> 00:40:15,459
你需要一位成熟和有智慧的人
You need someone older and wiser

418
00:40:15,695 --> 00:40:19,563
告诉你怎么做
Telling you what to do

419
00:40:19,799 --> 00:40:23,235
我17岁快18岁了
I am 17 going on 18

420
00:40:23,470 --> 00:40:29,431
我能够照顾你
I'll take care of you

421
00:41:01,975 --> 00:41:05,308
我16岁快17岁了
I am 16 going on 17

422
00:41:05,512 --> 00:41:08,913
我知道我很天真
I know that I'm naive

423
00:41:09,182 --> 00:41:12,413
我遇上的男孩或会说我很甜美
Fellows I meet May tell me I'm sweet

424
00:41:12,652 --> 00:41:16,349
我会心甘情愿地相信
And willingly I believe

425
00:41:16,823 --> 00:41:19,986
我16岁快17岁了
I am 16 going on 17

426
00:41:20,193 --> 00:41:23,959
如玫瑰般无邪
Innocent as a rose

427
00:41:24,164 --> 00:41:27,622
那些喝着白兰地的单身男子
Bachelor dandies Drinkers of brandies

428
00:41:27,934 --> 00:41:31,267
我对此毫无认识
What do I know of those?

429
00:41:31,471 --> 00:41:34,998
完全没有心理准备
Totally unprepared am I

430
00:41:35,275 --> 00:41:38,767
去面对男人的世界
To face a world of men

431
00:41:39,179 --> 00:41:42,512
我是如此怯懦，害羞和害怕
Timid and shy and scared am I

432
00:41:42,782 --> 00:41:46,445
事情全在我知识范围以外
Of things beyond my ken

433
00:41:46,886 --> 00:41:50,481
我需要一位成熟和有智慧的人
I need someone older and wiser

434
00:41:50,723 --> 00:41:54,022
告诉我怎么做
Telling me what to do

435
00:41:54,360 --> 00:41:58,057
你17岁快18岁了
You are 17 going on 18

436
00:41:58,298 --> 00:42:03,964
我会完全信赖你
I'll depend on you

437
00:43:57,016 --> 00:43:58,449
请进
Come in.

438
00:43:59,485 --> 00:44:01,112
思蜜德小姐
Frau Schmidt.

439
00:44:03,456 --> 00:44:05,185
这是给你做新衣服的
For your new dresses.

440
00:44:05,491 --> 00:44:09,484
-舰长从城里买来的 -多么美的布料
- The captain had these sent from town. - Oh, how lovely!

441
00:44:09,762 --> 00:44:13,198
我可以缝制出最漂亮的衣裳
These will make the prettiest clothes I've ever had.

442
00:44:13,466 --> 00:44:16,958
告诉我，如果我再要求 多点布料的话，他会肯吗？
Do you think he would get me more material if I asked?

443
00:44:17,203 --> 00:44:20,832
-家庭教师需要多少衣服？ -不是为我，是为了孩子
- How many dresses do you need? - Not for me, for the children.

444
00:44:21,107 --> 00:44:23,166
我要为他们做点游戏服
I want to make them some play clothes.

445
00:44:23,443 --> 00:44:26,970
范崔普的孩子不玩游戏 他们只做操练
The von Trapp children don't play. They march.

446
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:29,880
所以你不赞成了
Surely you don't approve of that.

447
00:44:30,883 --> 00:44:33,283
自从舰长失去他太太后
Ever since the captain lost his poor wife...

448
00:44:33,519 --> 00:44:36,215
他管理家事就好像管军舰般
...he runs this house as if on one of his ships.

449
00:44:37,056 --> 00:44:38,455
哨音、命令
Whistles, orders.

450
00:44:38,725 --> 00:44:40,556
再也没有音乐 没有欢笑了
No more music, no more laughing.

451
00:44:40,827 --> 00:44:44,354
不愿接触任何能让他 想起她的事物，孩子们也一样
Nothing that reminds him of her. Even the children.

452
00:44:44,864 --> 00:44:45,956
那太不对了
But that's so wrong.

453
00:44:46,799 --> 00:44:48,323
可以怎样？
Oh, well.

454
00:44:48,534 --> 00:44:52,197
你喜欢你的房间吗？ 你会有新的窗帘
How do you like your room? There'll be new drapes at the windows.

455
00:44:52,472 --> 00:44:53,734
它们还好好地
Bu these are fine.

456
00:44:53,973 --> 00:44:55,634
反正新的已经订了
New ones have been ordered.

457
00:44:55,842 --> 00:44:59,141
-我真的不需要它们 -晚安
- But I really don't need them. - Good night, now.

458
00:44:59,379 --> 00:45:03,406
思蜜德小姐，你想如果明天 我要求他布料的事
Frau Schmidt, if I asked the captain about the material?

459
00:45:03,683 --> 00:45:08,143
-他明早就离开去维也纳 -是，他要去多久呢？
- He's leaving in the morning. - Of course. How long will he be gone?

460
00:45:08,721 --> 00:45:13,317
那得看情况，上次他在男爵夫人 那儿停留了一个月
It depends. The last time he visited the baroness, he stayed for a month.

461
00:45:14,494 --> 00:45:19,056
我本不该说这些的 我们还不很熟悉
I shouldn't be saying this to you. I don't know you that well.

462
00:45:19,332 --> 00:45:22,233
但如果你问我的话 舰长是很认真地…
But if you ask me, the captain's thinking seriously...

463
00:45:22,435 --> 00:45:24,733
想娶这女人
...of marrying her before summer's over.

464
00:45:24,937 --> 00:45:28,168
那太好了 孩子们会有新母亲了
Wonderful! The children will have a mother again.

465
00:45:29,609 --> 00:45:30,906
是的
Yes.

466
00:45:31,177 --> 00:45:32,906
晚安
Well, good night.

467
00:45:33,112 --> 00:45:34,545
晚安
Good night.

468
00:45:53,020 --> 00:45:55,853
亲爱的天父 我现在知道为何你要我来此了
Dear Father, now I know why You sent me here.

469
00:45:56,090 --> 00:45:58,957
是帮助这些孩子 准备接受他们的新母亲
To help these children prepare for a new mother.

470
00:45:59,193 --> 00:46:02,492
而我也祈祷 它将会是个快乐的家庭
And I pray this will become a happy family in Thy sight.

471
00:46:02,697 --> 00:46:05,825
主保佑舰长，莉莎，费瑞克
God bless the captain. God bless Liesl and Friedrich.

472
00:46:06,033 --> 00:46:10,197
还有露易莎 碧姬塔，犸塔和小葛特儿
God bless Louisa, Brigitta, Marta and little Gretl.

473
00:46:10,505 --> 00:46:13,338
我忘了个男孩 他叫什么名字？
And I forgot the other boy. What's his name?

474
00:46:15,109 --> 00:46:16,940
总之，主保佑他
Well, God bless what's-his-name.

475
00:46:17,144 --> 00:46:21,137
求主赐福院长，犸格丽特修女
God bless the Reverend Mother and Sister Margaretta...

476
00:46:21,349 --> 00:46:23,146
和在修道院的每位修女
...and everybody at the abbey.

477
00:46:23,351 --> 00:46:25,876
还有主啊，有关莉莎
And now, dear God, about Liesl.

478
00:46:26,387 --> 00:46:28,287
让她知道我是她的朋友
Help her know that I'm her friend...

479
00:46:28,489 --> 00:46:31,049
让她告诉我，她在干什么
...and help her tell me what she's been up to.

480
00:46:31,792 --> 00:46:32,952
你会去告密吗？
Are you going to tell on me?

481
00:46:33,194 --> 00:46:36,630
协助我能了解，让我能指引她
Help me to be understanding so I may guide her footsteps.

482
00:46:36,898 --> 00:46:39,526
因父，及子，及圣神之名
In the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Ghost.

483
00:46:39,734 --> 00:46:42,726
我出去散步，而大门提前关
I was out walking and somebody locked the doors early.

484
00:46:43,037 --> 00:46:46,666
我不想吵醒大家 所以当我看见你的窗户是开着时…
I didn't want to wake everybody, so when I saw your window open...

485
00:46:48,309 --> 00:46:51,335
你不会向父亲告密吧？
You're not going to tell Father, are you?

486
00:46:57,418 --> 00:46:58,715
你是如何攀上来的？
How did you climb up?

487
00:46:59,220 --> 00:47:02,348
我们常这样进来戏弄家教
It's how we always got in to play tricks on the governess.

488
00:47:02,557 --> 00:47:05,549
露易莎能手拿一罐的蜘蛛 单手爬上来呢
Louisa can make it with a whole jar of spiders in her hand.

489
00:47:06,561 --> 00:47:08,222
蜘蛛？
Spiders?

490
00:47:11,933 --> 00:47:14,561
你是独自出去散步吗？
Were you out walking all by yourself?

491
00:47:22,043 --> 00:47:25,740
我们今晚将衣服洗好的话 明天就没有人会知道
If we wash that dress tonight, nobody would notice it tomorrow.

492
00:47:26,414 --> 00:47:28,177
你可以穿上这个
You could put this on.

493
00:47:29,917 --> 00:47:32,613
进去里面脱下衣服 泡在浴缸里
Take your dress and put it to soak in the bathtub.

494
00:47:32,853 --> 00:47:36,380
回来坐在床上，我们好好谈
Come back here and sit on the bed, and we'll have a talk.

495
00:47:37,692 --> 00:47:40,718
我今天告诉你，我不需要家教
I told you today I didn't need a governess.

496
00:47:40,928 --> 00:47:43,021
或许我还真的需要
Well, maybe I do.

497
00:48:13,494 --> 00:48:16,054
葛特儿，你害怕吗？
Gretl, are you scared?

498
00:48:19,567 --> 00:48:21,831
你不是怕这些雷电吧？
You're not frightened of a storm, are you?

499
00:48:22,069 --> 00:48:24,333
与我一起就不用怕了
You just stay right here with me.

500
00:48:25,506 --> 00:48:29,738
-其他的人呢？ -他们睡着了，他们不怕
- Where are the others? - They're asleep. They're not scared.

501
00:48:34,148 --> 00:48:35,979
是吗？看
Oh, no? Look.

502
00:48:37,518 --> 00:48:39,486
好吧，大家都上床来
All right, up here on the bed.

503
00:48:39,787 --> 00:48:42,483
-真的吗？ -只此一次，来吧
- Really? - Well, just this once. Come on.

504
00:48:43,591 --> 00:48:47,925
-现在就等男孩们 -他们不会来，男孩们是很勇敢的
- Now we'll wait for the boys. - You won't see them. Boys are brave.

505
00:48:54,001 --> 00:48:55,798
你们男孩不是也在害怕吧？
You weren't scared, were you?

506
00:48:56,337 --> 00:48:59,534
当然不怕 我们只想确定你不害怕
Oh, no. We just wanted to be sure that you weren't.

507
00:49:00,641 --> 00:49:03,667
-你真周到 -不是我出的主意
- That's very thoughtful of you. - It wasn't my idea.

508
00:49:03,978 --> 00:49:05,809
是寇特
It was Kurt's!

509
00:49:06,047 --> 00:49:08,641
寇特，是我忘掉的一位 主保佑寇特
Kurt! That's the one I left out! God bless Kurt.

510
00:49:11,452 --> 00:49:13,215
为何会这样？
Why does it do that?

511
00:49:13,454 --> 00:49:17,288
